      <hr><a name="skip_menu"></a><h1>521 - Target Audience Note (R)</h1>
      <hr>
      <div class="formatname">MARC 21 Bibliographic - Full</div>
      <div class="datename">October 2002</div>
      <hr>
      <table width="100%">
         <tr vAlign="top">
            <td width="45%"><strong>First Indicator</strong><br><em>Display constant controller</em><br># - Audience <br>0 - Reading grade level <br>1 - Interest age level <br>2 - Interest grade level <br>3 - Special audience characteristics <br>4 - Motivation/interest level <br>8 - No display constant generated <br><br></td>
            <td width="45%"><strong>Second Indicator</strong><br><em>Undefined</em><br># - Undefined <br><br></td>
         </tr>
      </table>
      <hr>
      <table width="100%">
         <tr vAlign="top">
            <td valign="top" width="50%" align="left"></td>
            <td valign="top" width="50%" align="left"></td>
         </tr>
         <tr vAlign="top">
            <td colspan="2"><strong>Subfield Codes</strong><br></td>
         </tr>
         <tr vAlign="top">
            <td colspan="1">$a - Target audience note (R) <br>$b - Source (NR) <br>$3 - Materials specified (NR) <br></td>
            <td colspan="1">$6 - Linkage (NR) <br>$8 - Field link and sequence number (R) <br></td>
         </tr>
   </table>
      <hr>
      <h3>FIELD DEFINITION AND SCOPE</h3>
      <p>Information that identifies the specific audience or intellectual level for which the
         content of the described item is considered appropriate.
      </p>
      <p>Used to record interest and motivation levels and special learner characteristics.
         Information about the target audience and/or intellectual level may also be recorded in
         coded form in field 008/22 (Target audience) for some types of material. (Note: If a
         computer files or visual materials record has both reading grade and interest age or
            interest grade level information present in 521 fields, field 008/22 is coded based on
                     the interest age information.) Notes that include restrictions on access are recorded in
                     field 506 (Restrictions on Access Note).
      </p>
      <p>The note is sometimes displayed and/or printed with an introductory term that is
                     generated as a display constant based on the first indicator value.      </p>
      <hr>
      <h3>GUIDELINES FOR APPLYING CONTENT DESIGNATORS</h3>
      <h4><span class="box">&#9632;</span> INDICATORS
      </h4>
      <div class="indicator"><strong>First Indicator - Display constant controller</strong> <div class="description">Controls the generation of a display constant preceding the note.
            <div class="indicatorvalue"><strong># - Audience</strong> <div class="description">Used to generate the display constant <em>Audience:</em>.
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="indicatorvalue"><strong>0 - Reading grade level</strong> <div class="description">Numbered information in subfield $a pertains to the grade level at
                                       which the item is meant to be read. The value is used to generate the display
                                       constant <em>Reading grade level:</em>.
                  <div class="example">
                     <table width="100%">
                        <tr>
                           <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="15%" align="left"></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>521</strong></td>
                           <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>0#</strong><strong>$a</strong>3.1.<br><em>[The reading level is that for the first month of the third
                                                      grade.]</em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="indicatorvalue"><strong>1 - Interest age level</strong> <div class="description">Numbered information in subfield $a pertains to the age level at
                                       which the item will most likely be of interest. The value is used to generate
                                       the display constant <em>Interest age level:</em>.
                  <div class="example">
                     <table width="100%">
                        <tr>
                           <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="15%" align="left"></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>521</strong></td>
                           <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>1#</strong><strong>$a</strong>008-012.<br><em>[The item is of interest to those ages 8-12.]</em></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>521</strong></td>
                           <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>1#</strong><strong>$a</strong>7-10.<br><em>[The item is of interest to those ages 7-10.]</em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="indicatorvalue"><strong>2 - Interest grade level</strong> <div class="description">Numbered information in subfield $a pertains to the grade level at
                                       which the item will most likely be of interest. The value is used to generate
                                       the display constant <em>Interest grade level:</em>.
                  <div class="example">
                     <table width="100%">
                        <tr>
                           <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="15%" align="left"></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>521</strong></td>
                           <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>2#</strong><strong>$a</strong>7 &amp; up.<br><em>[The item is of interest to those in the seventh grade and up.]</em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="indicatorvalue"><strong>3 - Special audience characteristics</strong> <div class="description">Pertains to special characteristics of the audience to which the item will most
                                       likely be of interest. The value is used to generate the display constant
                                          <em>Special audience characteristics:</em>.
                  <div class="example">
                     <table width="100%">
                        <tr>
                           <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="15%" align="left"></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>521</strong></td>
                           <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>3#</strong><strong>$a</strong>Vision impaired<strong>$a</strong>fine motor skills impaired<strong>$a</strong>audio learner<strong>$b</strong>LENOCA.<br><em>[The item is of interest to vision and fine motor skills impaired audio
                                                         learners.]</em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="indicatorvalue"><strong>4 - Motivation/interest level</strong> <div class="description">Identifies the motivation and/or interest level of the audience for which the
                                       item is best suited. The value is used to generate the display constant
                                          <em>Motivation/interest level:</em>.
                  <div class="example">
                     <table width="100%">
                        <tr>
                           <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="15%" align="left"></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>521</strong></td>
                           <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>4#</strong><strong>$a</strong>Highly motivated<strong>$a</strong>high interest<strong>$b</strong>LENOCA.<br><em>[The item is appropriate for highly motivated, highly interested
                                                         audience.] </em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="indicatorvalue"><strong>8 - No display constant generated</strong> </div>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="indicator"><strong>Second Indicator - Undefined</strong> <div class="description">Undefined and contains a blank (#).
            </div>
      </div>
