      <hr>
      <h3>INPUT CONVENTIONS</h3>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Punctuation</strong> - Field 521 ends with a period unless another mark of punctuation is present.
      </div>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Display Constants</strong> - Introductory terms such as <em>Audience:</em>, <em>Reading grade level:</em>, etc. are
                     not carried in the MARC record. They may be system generated as a display constant
                     associated with the first indicator value.
         <div class="table">
            <table>
               <tr>
                  <td width="170" align="left" valign="top"><u>First indicator</u></td>
                  <td width="399" align="left" valign="top"><u>Display constant</u></td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">#</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Audience:</td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">0</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Reading grade level:</td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">1</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Interest age level:</td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">2</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Interest grade level:</td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">3</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Special audience characteristics:</td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">4</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Motivation/interest level:</td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">8</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left"><em>[no display constant]</em></td>
               </tr>
